# SafeHer Mobile App — Implementation Plan

## Overview
A full-featured women's safety React Native (Expo) app for iOS + Android.  
All emergency features work **offline-first**. Community features require internet.  
Preference: **free/open-source APIs only** wherever possible.

---

## Free API Strategy

| Need | Free Solution |
|------|--------------|
| SMS alerts | `expo-sms` (native, no cost) + Android Telephony for auto-call |
| Email alerts | EmailJS (free tier 200/month) or SMTP via NodeMailer (self-hosted) |
| Push notifications | Firebase FCM (free) |
| Maps | OpenStreetMap + react-native-maps (free) |
| Directions / Route | OSRM open-source routing (free) OR Google Maps ($200 credit/mo free) |
| Geocoding | Nominatim (OSM, free) |
| Auth | Firebase Auth (free tier) |
| Database | Supabase (free tier: 500MB DB, 1GB storage) |
| Real-time | Supabase Realtime (free) |
| Voice keyword | Vosk offline ASR (open-source, free) |
| Emergency call | `expo-phone` / native `Linking.openURL('tel:112')` |
| Crash reporting | Sentry (free tier) |

